{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17644328","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17644328"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T20:04:11+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T20:04:11+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18040"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18040","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18040"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.05,0.05,0.05,0.81,0.05]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10754"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74140"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10754","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10754"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18040"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59631"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"4946"},{"type":"tags","id":"8407"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25087"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25090"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74140","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/74140"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the histological appearance of osteons?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Network of collagen fibres","Clusters of osteoclasts","Flat sheets of bone matrix","Cylindrical structures with concentric lamellae","Irregular trabecular meshwork"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Ecylindrical structures with concentric lamellae\u003C/strong\u003E represent osteons, which form the essential building blocks of compact bone tissue. Each unit is arranged as a series of concentric rings of mineralised matrix (lamellae) that surround a central Haversian canal containing neurovascular elements.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe other options are incorrect because:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIrregular trabecular meshwork\u003C/strong\u003E describes cancellous bone architecture rather than the organised structure of osteons in compact bone\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFlat sheets of bone matrix\u003C/strong\u003E fails to capture the three-dimensional cylindrical organisation of osteonal systems\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EClusters of osteoclasts\u003C/strong\u003E describes bone-resorbing cells rather than the structural organisation of bone tissue\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENetwork of collagen fibres\u003C/strong\u003E describes only one component of bone matrix without capturing the complex organised structure of complete osteons\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EUnderstanding the histological structure of osteons is crucial as they provide both the structural framework and the mechanism for nutrient delivery in compact bone tissue.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The basic structural and functional unit of compact bone is the osteon (Haversian system).","Each osteon has a cylindrical shape made up of rings of mineralised matrix called lamellae.","Blood vessels and nerve fibres run through the central Haversian canal of each osteon."],"references":["Gartner, L. P. (2020). Textbook of histology e-book: Textbook of histology e-book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Baig MA, Bacha D. Histology, Bone. 2023 May 1. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 31082176","Blumer MJF. Bone tissue and histological and molecular events during development of the long bones. Ann Anat. 2021 May;235:151704. doi: 10.1016/j.aanat.2021.151704. Epub 2021 Feb 16. PMID: 33600952","Florencio-Silva R, Sasso GR, Sasso-Cerri E, Sim\u00f5es MJ, Cerri PS. Biology of Bone Tissue: Structure, Function, and Factors That Influence Bone Cells. Biomed Res Int. 2015;2015:421746. doi: 10.1155/2015/421746. Epub 2015 Jul 13. PMID: 26247020; PMCID: PMC4515490"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59631"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18040"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59631","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/59631"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-24T21:32:33+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-24T21:33:42+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10754"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74140"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading